    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="845"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d845">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/122a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        German Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1919</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Refferring to previous correspondence
                    concerning the action of the British authorities in removing from the American
                    S. S. <hi rend="italic">China</hi> certain German and Austro-Hungarian subjects,
                    I have the honor to inquire whether you can inform me whether any of the persons
                    removed from that vessel were incorporated in the armed forces of Germany,
                    Austria, or Turkey.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
